\section{Business Understanding}

\subsection{Domain Context and Business Value}
Planwisely B.V. is a planning and scheduling platform provider that develops 
solutions for manufacturing companies. It enables their customers with AI tools to 
determine the order and machine assignment of production orders. The company also 
offers a demand planning tool to manage demand forecasts and production scheduling. 
The client in this project is a confectionery manufacturer.

Demand forecasting takes a central role in supply chain management. It helps 
companies to match supply with expected demand and avoid the costs of overstocking 
and stockouts \citep{lewis2012demand}. In the food industry, and in confectionery in 
particular, this problem is especially relevant. Products have defined shelf lives, 
demand is sensitive to both internal and external factors, and distribution channels 
are usually very diverse \citep{nassibi2023demand}.

The business value of an improved forecasting model is direct. Overestimation leads 
to excess stock and potential waste, while underestimation leads to stockouts, lost 
revenue, and weakened retailer and customer relationships \citep{amosu2024}. Apart 
from accuracy, the explainability of predictions enables validated reasoning, 
long-term adjustments, and better communication within planning teams 
\citep{theissler2022}. This is the gap the artefact in this project is designed 
to fill.

\subsection{Existing Solutions}
An analysis of existing demand forecasting tools reveals two major categories.

The first category consists of traditional statistical tools, such as Excel-based 
forecasting, ERP modules, and classical time series methods. These approaches are 
commonly used due to their simplicity and low barrier to entry. However, they are 
limited in their ability to capture complex, non-linear demand patterns 
\citep{armstrong2005demand}.

The second category consists of advanced machine learning and AI forecasting 
solutions. While such methods offer high predictive 
accuracy, they provide limited transparency into how forecasts are generated and 
require significant technical expertise to implement and maintain 
\citep{carbonneau2008application}.

The gap this project addresses is the combination of these two categories: a system 
that achieves the accuracy of complex models while providing the interpretability of 
simpler tools, packaged in an accessible interface designed for non-technical users.

